properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 2 at 3:26AM PST until February 2 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Gusty Northerly Winds across the Valley on Sunday...

.A strong upper trough moving through on Sunday will bring a
period of gusty northerly winds. Expected wind gusts are likely
to reach 30 to 45 mph at times from the late morning through the
evening. Breezy conditions to continue into Monday as the system
exits toward the southwestern U.S.

* WHAT...Northerly winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts around 30 to 45
mph expected.

* WHERE...Sacramento Valley, Carquinez Strait and Delta,
Northern San Joaquin Valley and Northeast Foothills/Sacramento
Valley Counties.

* WHEN...From 10 AM to 7 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result. Expect difficult driving conditions at times.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THIS MORNING TO 7 PM PST THIS EVENING
